data.title: Cycurion partners with NACCHO for cybersecurity webinars, empowering healthcare orgs with threat intelligence. VP Eric Singleton leads series.
data.description: Cycurion, Inc., a prominent technology and staffing solutions provider for the public sector trading on NASDAQ under the symbol CYCU, based in McLean, Virginia, revealed an extensive cybersecurity education program on Oct. 30, 2025. The initiative, developed in collaboration with the National Association of County and City Health Officials (NACCHO), aims to equip healthcare entities with essential threat intelligence and defense tactics. The educational effort comprises a trio of webinars headed by industry expert Eric Singleton, who serves as the Vice President of Operations at Cycurion. This move underscores Cycurion's commitment to promoting proactive cybersecurity awareness and arming public sector officials with the knowledge to counter advancing digital threats.

data.title: SurgePays launches Growth Marketing & Data Partnerships division led by James Herber for monetizing data, expanding revenue opportunities.
data.description: A new project, spearheaded by experienced industry leader James Herber, is boosting the monetization of SurgePays' data ecosystem. This venture aims to capitalize on high-margin recurring revenue options, thereby enhancing the company's financial prospects. The initiative is expected to significantly increase SurgePays' earnings and broaden its scope for profitability.

data.title: House of Doge and Brag House Holdings confirm Triestina sponsorship with Dogecoin as primary kit & stadium mark, also confirm equity acquisition.
data.description: Today in New York and Miami, House of Doge Inc., the corporate entity of the Dogecoin Foundation, has revealed a partnership with Brag House Holdings, Inc. (NASDAQ: TBH) and U.S. Triestina Calcio 1918, introducing a multi-asset sponsorship deal. This arrangement will prominently display Dogecoin on the front of the club’s official match jerseys, accompanied by House of Doge branding on specific secondary placements. Following House of Doge’s recent acquisition of equity in Triestina, marking the first instance of a cryptocurrency company holding a significant stake in a professional football club, this sponsorship will be active from the current season through the 2026/27 campaign.

data.title: Telegram launches Cocoon on TON blockchain for decentralized AI inference, enhancing private computation with strong user base and GPU support.
data.description: Telegram recently launched Cocoon, a decentralized AI inference network on the TON blockchain. The platform is designed to enhance private AI computation by leveraging a strong user base and GPU contributions. This initiative is expected to revolutionize the field of AI with its focus on privacy and performance.

data.title: Character.AI suspends teen chats in response to legal pressure, banning minors from open-ended chat due to regulatory scrutiny.
data.description: After facing multiple lawsuits and growing regulatory pressure, Character.AI has announced that it will prohibit individuals under the age of 18 from accessing its unrestricted chat function. This decision comes after a prolonged period of legal challenges and government scrutiny.

data.title: IQSTEL projects $430M in 2026 revenue (26% growth from $340M in 2025) due to organic expansion, plans to achieve $15M EBITDA.
data.description: IQSTEL Inc. announced a 2026 organic revenue forecast of $430 million, a 26% increase from the $340 million forecast for 2025. In 2024, IQSTEL reported $283 million in revenue and is on track to meet the $340 million 2025 forecast. The company plans to acquire two to three businesses to achieve $15 million in EBITDA by 2026, focusing on profitable organic growth. CEO Leandro Iglesias stated the forecast reflects their ability to deliver consistent organic growth and build towards sustained profitability. IQSTEL operates in over 20 countries, serving 600+ telecom operators, with plans to become a $1 billion revenue company.

data.title: Neogen names Bryan Riggsbee as CFO, effective Nov 3, 2025. Riggsbee to oversee global finance, reporting to CEO Mike Nassif.
data.description: Neogen® Corporation, a renowned provider of food safety solutions, has designated Bryan Riggsbee as its new Chief Financial Officer, taking effect on November 3, 2025. Riggsbee, who will lead Neogen’s worldwide finance division, will become a part of the Executive Leadership Team and will directly report to CEO Mike Nassif. The current CFO, David Naemura, is anticipated to stay with the company until the transition is completed. Neogen® Corporation operates with the ticker symbol NEOG on NASDAQ.

data.title: Dow futures decline after Fed rate cuts and Trump-Xi meeting. S&P 500 and Nasdaq swing. Amazon and Apple earnings in focus. Fed likely to cut interest rates in December. Treasury bond yields: 10yr at 4.07%, 2yr at 3.59%. Alphabet stock soars post strong Q3 results.
data.description: US stock futures fluctuated on Thursday following mixed moves. The meeting between President Trump and President Xi Jinping resulted in reduced US fentanyl tariffs in exchange for increased soybean imports from China, a deal on rare earths, and positive indications for a broader trade deal. However, Fed Chair Powell's cautionary speech weighed on stocks as he hinted another rate cut isn't certain. The 10-year Treasury bond yielded 4.07% and the two-year bond stood at 3.59%. FedWatch projected a 70.4% likelihood of a rate cut in December. Futures changes were Dow Jones -0.19%, S&P 500 0.03%, Nasdaq 100 0.06%, and Russell 2000 0.36%. SPY and QQQ tracking ETFs were mixed in premarket. Alphabet Inc. soared 7.57% after beating Q3 estimates with $102.35B revenue and $2.87 EPS.

data.title: Trillions expected to transfer from Silent Generation & Baby Boomers to younger generations, survey reveals generational wealth transfer expectations & estate planning preparedness gaps. 60% under 59 expect inheritance, 64% over 60 plan to pass wealth. 21% over 60 do not plan to pass down, 94% not working with financial advisor.
data.description: The Great Wealth Transfer is set to move trillions of dollars from the Silent Generation and Baby Boomers to younger generations, prompting a need for better inheritance planning. MDRT surveyed 2,000 U.S. consumers across generations to understand readiness for this shift. 60% of consumers under 59 expect inheritance, while 64% of those above 60 plan to pass down wealth. Notably, 21% of older consumers don't plan to transfer wealth, with 94% not utilizing a financial advisor. This highlights generational differences in estate planning preparedness and the need for financial advice in navigating wealth transfers.

data.title: Meta Platforms Inc. (NASDAQ: META) beats Q3 earnings estimates with $1.05 EPS (adjusted $7.25 EPS) and $51.24 billion revenue, surpassing $49.38 billion estimate and increasing by 26.25% from last year.
data.description: Meta Platforms Inc. (NASDAQ: META) released positive third-quarter earnings on Wednesday. The company reported diluted earnings per share of $1.05, reflecting a one-time, non-cash income tax charge of $15.93 billion. This figure may not align with the estimated $6.68. Adjusted earnings per share stood at $7.25. Quarterly revenue reached $51.24 billion, surpassing the estimated $49.38 billion and marking a 26.25% increase from last year's $40.58 billion. The company expressed satisfaction with their performance during the quarter. For more details, visit Benzinga.com.

data.title: HanesBrands to report Q3 fiscal 2025 results on Nov 6, 2025. Acquisition by Gildan Activewear Inc. announced. No conference call.
data.description: HanesBrands Inc. (NYSE: HBI) has shared its intention to disclose the financial outcomes for the third quarter of fiscal 2025 on Thursday, November 6, 2025, prior to the market opening through a press release. Due to the impending procurement of HanesBrands Inc. by Gildan Activewear Inc. in August 2025, no conference call will be conducted. The press release can be accessed in the Investors segment of the HanesBrands corporate website at www.hanes.com/investo.
